cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.EC

This paper studies mechanisms for resource allocation, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of greedy allocation rules is a common technique in algorithm design, which further supports the inclusion of cs.DS. The paper also discusses the efficiency of these mechanisms, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper analyzes the price of anarchy, which is a concept in economic theory (cs.EC).
